    <!-- ===== Per-OEM battery guidance (M8.4 reliability) ===== -->
    <string name="settings_oem_title">Extra steps for this phone</string>
    <string name="settings_oem_samsung_intro">Samsung (One UI) has its own sleep/hibernation layer on top of Android\'s battery optimization — the exemption above isn\'t always enough. For reliable always-listening:</string>
    <string name="settings_oem_samsung_step1">1. Settings → Battery → Background usage limits → remove Live Ninja from Sleeping apps (or add it to Never sleeping apps).</string>
    <string name="settings_oem_samsung_step2">2. App info → Battery → set to Unrestricted.</string>
    <string name="settings_oem_samsung_step3">3. Settings → Battery → Background usage limits → turn off \"Put unused apps to sleep\" so this and other settings don\'t get reset automatically.</string>
    <string name="settings_oem_generic_intro">Some phone makers add their own background-app limits on top of Android\'s. If wake-word listening keeps stopping, check your phone\'s battery settings for Live Ninja and exempt it from any \"sleeping apps\" / background-limit list, using the button above.</string>
    <string name="settings_oem_app_info_action">Open Live Ninja app info</string>

